en_880456_0	At the request of the Sri Lanka Transport Board (SLTB), the Army on the instructions of the Commander of the Army Wednesday (8) afternoon made 28 Army buses available to the SLTB for passage of stranded civilians in Colombo and elsewhere after a section of railway employees launched a lightning strike over some trade union issues.
en_880456_1	Those buses, manned by Army personnel enabled passengers and school students to travel free of charge to their destinations in Galle, Kandy, Chilaw, Kurunegala, Nittambuwa, Rambukkana, Mirigama, Veyangoda, Giriulla, Gampaha, Ganemulla and Polgahawela areas.
en_880456_2	Similarly, a fleet of 44 Army buses have been placed on standby in the event the SLTB requests the services of those buses during the course of Thursday (9) according to the Military Spokesman, Brigadier Sumith Atapattu.
